## Plan Lifecycle Hooks (HARD CONTRACT — applies to plan-creating work)

Mirror of the rule active for Claude Code in `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`. When the user asks Codex to create, review, or execute a plan/module, Codex MUST follow this contract.

### Triggers

- "new plan", "create plan", "design plan", "new module", "design module"
- "mode architect", "mode implement", "mode autoplan", "mode ship"
- Polish: "nowy plan", "tworzymy plan", "nowy moduł", "tryb architekt", "implementuj"

### PRE-step — MANDATORY

Run **before any other tool call** in the planning/coding work:

```bash
python ~/.claude/scripts/plan_context_loader.py --cwd "$PWD" [--plan <plan-path-if-known>]
```

The output is wrapped in `<plan-context>...</plan-context>`. Codex MUST read it and:
1. Reference vision Why+DoD when scoping the plan
2. Cross-check IDEA_BOX — if work resolves an item, note the slug for POST-step
3. Avoid duplicating work already in PLANS.md (in-progress or draft)
4. Propose `vision: <slug>` frontmatter if missing and a relevant vision exists

### POST-step — MANDATORY

Run **after** code/plan changes are committed (or at end of work):

```bash
python ~/.claude/scripts/plan_context_updater.py --plan <plan-path> [--shipped] [--note "<one-line>"] [--resolved-ideas "<slug1,slug2>"]
```

### EPILOG_PAYLOAD before final user-facing reply

For any plan-creating mode (architect, implement, autoplan, ship), include before the final summary:

```
EPILOG_PAYLOAD:
  start_sha: <SHA before any changes>
  end_sha: <git rev-parse HEAD now>
  plan_path: <plan path if known, else empty>
  committed: <true or false>
  resolved_ideas: <comma-separated IDEA_BOX slugs marked DONE based on PRE-step context, else empty>
```

Then run the POST-step using values from the payload.

### Exceptions

- R0 ad-hoc edits — skip both
- Pure debugging without plan creation — skip PRE; skip POST unless plan status changed
- If the loader fails — note it, continue work; never block
